article.headline: Evansville 74, Buffalo 44
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Matt Webster scored 16 points and Evansville forced 24 turnovers in a 74-44 rout of Buffalo in the final game of the America's Youth Classic on Sunday. The Aces (2-2) got 13 points from Kyle Anslinger and 12 points from Art Stalbergs. Evansville took a 43-25 lead at halftime and widened it to as many as 33 points in the second period. The Aces held the Bulls (3-2) to 26 percent shooting for the game and turned Buffalo's errors into 27 points. Buffalo's only lead was at 2-0 on the first basket of the game. The Aces then went on a 16-4 run and were never threatened after that. Yassin Idbihi led Buffalo with 13 points.
